Gender Hierarchy in Fiction: A Replication of Kraicer and Piper, 2019: Social Characters: The Hierarchy of Gender in Contemporary English-Language Fiction

Hannah Hardenbergh

5/10/2019

This file contains code that replicates the first table and first four figures of Kraicer and Pipers report on how gender bias has found its way into contemporary fiction. The scope of this project is to enhance the figures that give the paper as a whole a more understandable visual for its readers. Kraicer and Piper establish several assertions; my goal with this replication is to simply provide readers a more accurate description of the underrepresentation of female-gendered characters in contemporary novels so that Kraicer and Pipers foundation for their statistical analyses is crystal-clear. Their paper could use improvements in other areas as well, and their data continued to be cleaned, certainly an area for future research.
